      "parameters": {
        "content": "# S6 \u2014 Exercise: Refactor 10 Nodes Into 1 Code Node\n\n## The challenge\nYou're given a sales pipeline that uses **10+ core nodes** to:\n1. Filter orders by status\n2. Calculate tax (15%)\n3. Add a discount for orders > $200\n4. Format customer names\n5. Compute the grand total\n\nYour job: **rebuild the entire BEFORE branch as a single Code node** in the AFTER branch \u2014 and prove the outputs match.\n\n## How to use\n- \u25b6\ufe0f Click 'Run Exercise' \u2192 both branches execute\n- Compare outputs of `BEFORE: Final Output` vs `AFTER: Code Node Solution`\n- They should be identical\n- Try doing it yourself FIRST in `AFTER: Your Solution Here` before peeking at the reference\n\n## Why this matters\n- Fewer nodes = easier to read, faster to run, easier to debug\n- BUT: Code nodes hide logic from non-coders \u2192 use judgment\n- **Rule of thumb:** if you're chaining 4+ Set/IF/Filter nodes for one transformation, switch to Code.",
        "width": 620,
        "height": 440,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "ea5b4ca9-dbe2-401e-b893-bb22c8c9a26f",
