    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "javaScript",
        "mode": "runOnceForAllItems",
        "jsCode": "// \ud83d\udc47 YOUR TURN\n// Replicate the BEFORE branch in this single Code node.\n// Steps:\n//   1. Get all items\n//   2. Filter status === 'paid'\n//   3. Add 15% tax\n//   4. If amount > 200, apply 10% discount\n//   5. Title-case the customer name\n//   6. Return {id, customer, final_amount}\n\nconst items = $input.all();\n\n// TODO: write your transformation here\nreturn items;\n"
      },
      "id": "d8435ce8-9b65-4e23-b836-96fd220139dd",
      "name": "AFTER: Your Solution Here",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        480,
        520
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "javaScript",
        "mode": "runOnceForAllItems",
        "jsCode": "// \u2705 Reference solution \u2014 same output as the 10-node BEFORE branch\nconst titleCase = s => s.split(' ').map(w => w[0].toUpperCase() + w.slice(1)).join(' ');\n\nreturn $input.all()\n  .filter(i => i.json.status === 'paid')\n  .map(i => {\n    const withTax = i.json.amount * 1.15;\n    const final = i.json.amount > 200 ? withTax * 0.9 : withTax;\n    return {\n      json: {\n        id: i.json.id,\n        customer: titleCase(i.json.customer),\n        final_amount: Math.round(final * 100) / 100\n      }\n    };\n  });\n"
      },
      "id": "37d32e76-14e4-4bbb-b7ef-19d657d3846d",
      "name": "AFTER: Reference Solution",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        720,
        520
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "python",
        "mode": "runOnceForAllItems",
        "pythonCode": "# Same logic in Python\ndef title_case(s): return ' '.join(w.capitalize() for w in s.split())\n\nresult = []\nfor item in _input.all():\n    data = item.json\n    if data['status'] != 'paid':\n        continue\n    with_tax = data['amount'] * 1.15\n    final = with_tax * 0.9 if data['amount'] > 200 else with_tax\n    result.append({'json': {\n        'id': data['id'],\n        'customer': title_case(data['customer']),\n        'final_amount': round(final, 2)\n    }})\n\nreturn result\n"
      },
      "id": "6b5c095e-3088-409d-8bc2-844a31311b8a",
      "name": "AFTER: Python Equivalent",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        960,
        520
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## \ud83d\udca1 Lessons learned\n\n**10 nodes \u2192 1 node**\n\n- Filter, map, conditional logic, name formatting, and field selection all happen in **one place**\n- Easier to test, easier to read, easier to version-control\n- The Python version is identical \u2014 pick the language you're more fluent in\n- \u26a0\ufe0f But: a non-coder reviewing your workflow now needs to read code. Tradeoff.\n\n## When to refactor to Code\n- 4+ chained Set / IF / Filter nodes for one transformation\n- Logic that's hard to express in expressions\n- You need loops, recursion, or complex conditionals\n\n## When to KEEP core nodes\n- Logic non-developers must read/edit\n- Each step is meaningfully distinct and worth visualizing",
        "width": 520,
        "height": 520,
        "color": 5
      },
